English:
@d0<color=#00ffff>Log 1474:</color>
While the containment system is working perfectly, there is still concern among some of the staff that contagions could get out. I have tried to offer my assurances to those who work under me, but they do not trust me. How do I make them trust me?
@p9 @d0<color=#00ffff>Log 1475:</color>
There was an... incident today. A power spike caused one of the containment forcefields to momentarily fail. Dr. Weston was present to handle the situation with the skill and professionalism I've come to expect. We've since installed power upgrades to prevent further outages.
@p9 @d0<color=#00ffff>Log 1476:</color>
Everyone has been on edge as of late. Perhaps we've been running on too much coffee, or not enough. I sent 2 of the interns to check up on the local Zirax drone base. No change in drone activity. I still wonder why the Zirax abandoned their colonization plans for this place. Perhaps they didn't like the cold.

Chinese (simplified):
@d0 <color=#00ffff>Log 1474:</color>
虽然收容系统运行良好,但一些工作人员仍然担心传染源可能会扩散出去.我试图取得下属的信任,但他们并不信任我。我怎样才能让他们相信我?
@p9 @d0 <color=#00ffff>Log 1475:</color>
今天发生了...一点小事故。一次能量激增导致其中一个收容力场暂时失效。Weston博士正如我期待的那样,用他的技巧和专业精神处理了这一情况。此后我们升级了电力系统,以防止进一步停电.
@p9 @d0 <color=#00ffff>Log 1476:</color>
最近大家都处于紧张状态。也许我们喝了太多咖啡,又或者是喝得不够。我派了两名实习生去检查当地的兹瑞克斯无人机基地。无人机活动没有变化。我仍然想知道为什么兹瑞克斯人放弃了他们对这个地方的殖民计划,也许他们不喜欢寒冷.

English:
@d0<color=#00ffff>Log 1477:</color>
Weston has fallen ill. It appears to be a common cold but he's been confined to quarters as a precaution. Study of the cryopods and the alien creatures contained within continues. They seem to have a fascinating ability to withstand the rigors of the extreme cold. It's possible they could even survive in the harsh vacuum of space itself.
@p9 @d0<color=#00ffff>Log 1478:</color>
We have ordered Dr. Weston transported back to the colony ship as we do not yet have the medical facilities to properly treat his condition. A fight broke out in the mess hall today. Something about eating the last Space Fry or some such. I don't have time for this. The security chief better do his job.
@p9 @d0<color=#00ffff>Log 1479:</color>
The Alien cryopods we discovered buried in the ice continue to fascinate me. We've detected minute power fluctuations within the pods themselves. Curiously, these power fluctuations occur in all 5 pods simultaneously. I proposed to the expedition leader that we dissect one of the specimens. He agreed, but asked me to write up a risk assessment first. Something about safety protocol.

Chinese (simplified):
@d0 <color=#00ffff>Log 1477:</color>
Weston也病倒了,虽然看上去只是普通感冒,但以防万一,他现在被隔离在宿舍里。对冷冻舱和其中包含的外星生物的研究仍在继续。它们似乎有一种令人着迷的能力,能够抵御极寒的严酷考验。它们甚至有可能在太空本身的严酷真空中生存.
@p9 @d0 <color=#00ffff>Log 1478:</color>
我已经下令把Weston 博士送回殖民船,毕竟我们手上没有可以处理这种状况的医疗设备.今天食堂发生了一场斗殴,好像是关于吃最后一个太空炸薯条之类的事情,我可没有闲心管这种事,安全主管最好能处理好他的工作.
@p9 @d0 <color=#00ffff>Log 1479:</color>
发掘出的冷冻舱依旧令我着迷。我们检测到5个舱内均存在微小的功率波动。但奇怪的是,这些功率波动同时发生在所有5个吊舱中。我向探险队领队提议我们解剖其中一个标本。他同意了,但要求我先写一份风险评估。关于安全协议的之类的.

English:
@d0<color=#00ffff>Log 1480:</color>
We were prepared to open one of the pods and carefully remove the alien contained within when Security Chief Newern burst into the room and put a stop to it all. Shortsighted men who lack vision... When I demanded to know why, all he'd say was there was an emergency situation and to perform no further research.
@p9 @d0<color=#00ffff>Log 1481:</color>
Undeterred by yesterday's interruption, I ordered research to resume. There's too much at stake to stop now. The work we're doing here could save humanity. Think of the potential! Think of the life saving gene therapies we could develop. They say they lost contact with the colony ship, but I fail to see how that has anything to do with my work down here...
@p9 @d0<color=#00ffff>Log 1482:</color>
This will be my final log. The fear mankind has of the unknown has won out today. We have all been ordered confined to quarters by our so-called commander. They are just afraid, afraid of what I'll discover. Afraid of what I MUST discover. If I had my way I'd throw them all out into the cold! Small men getting in the way of MY greatness! The world will know the name Dr. Chan!
@p9 @d0The log ends.

Chinese (simplified):
@d0 <color=#00ffff>Log 1480:</color>
我们正准备打开其中一个冷冻舱并小心地取出其中的外星生命,但就在这时安全主管Newern冲进房间,制止了这一切。目光短浅的人……当我询问原因时,他只是说有紧急情况,不要进行一步研究.
@p9 @d0 <color=#00ffff>Log 1481:</color>
我并没有被昨天的中断吓倒,而是下令恢复研究,现在已经不能回头了。我们在这里所做的工作可以拯救人类。想想他们的潜力!想想我们可以开发的的基因疗法能拯救多少生命。他们说他们与殖民船失去了联系,但这与我在这里的工作又有什么关系呢...
@p9 @d0 <color=#00ffff>Log 1482:</color>
这是我最后一条日志了,人类对未知事物的恐惧在今天已经胜出。我们所谓的指挥官命令我们所有人在宿舍里隔离。他们只是害怕罢了,害怕我会发现什么。害怕我一定会发现的东西。如果我有办法的话,我会把他们都扔到外面去!这些小人妨碍了我的伟大事业!全世界都会知道我Chan博士的大名!
@p9 @d0 日志结束.

English:
@d0<size=150%><color=#00ffff>Log 222:</color></size>
Ever since they brought back those blasted things and stuck them in the basement, the base's been experiencing power surges like crazy!
Spent 14 hours yesterday trying to fix it. I've come up with only 1 solution: Get rid of our alien 'cargo'.
@p9 @d0<size=150%><color=#00ffff>Log 223:</color></size>
I don't know what part of <b><color=#ffffff>the power grid can't handle it</color></b> these researchers don't understand. Do they think power can just teleport through the air like magic? I mean, it can, but it requires an intricate system of quantum tunnels and capacitors. This is the 14th power conduit to fail this week alone. Sooner or later those containment fields are going to fail and then we'll all be in trouble. Who's idea was this?

Chinese (simplified):
@d0 <size=150%><color=#00ffff>Log 222:</color></size>
自从他们把那些该死的东西带回来并把它们塞进地下室以来,基地就一直在经历疯狂的电涌!
昨天我花了14个小时试图修复它,我只能想出一个解决方案:那就是摆脱我们的外星“货物”.
@p9 @d0 <size=150%><color=#00ffff>Log 223:</color></size>
我也不知道究竟是电网的 <b><color=#ffffff>哪个部分扛不住了</color></b>这些研究人员难道完全不懂?他们认为电力可以像魔法一样在空中传送吗?当然我不是说不行,但那就需要一套复杂的量子隧道和电容器系统。这已经是本周发生的第14 次电力通路故障了。这些收容场迟早会失效,然后我们都会陷入麻烦,究竟是谁的主意?

