English:
@d0<color=#00ff00>This experimental neural interface allows between 1 to 4 participants to experience a virtual reality simulation of the last moments of a soldier's life.</color>
<color=#00ff00>The virtual reality construct is experimental in nature so it is vital that all participants stay as close as possible to each other to avoid breaking the virtual reality matrix. You can make multiple attempts if you do not succeed on your first.</color>
@p9 @d0<color=#00ff00>The interface portal will remain open for 2 minutes upon activation, and then stay closed for 5 minutes. Make sure all participants are ready and well equipped before entering the simulation.</color>
<color=#00ff00>Make sure all participants are wearing their preferred armor with full durability before entering the simulation.</color>
@p9 @d0<color=#00ff00>Before entering the simulation, all participants should make sure the mission </color><color=#ff00ff>The Dead Chapter 2</color><color=#00ff00> is currently active in their PDA. You will have 60 minutes to successfully complete the simulation before you must start over. </color>
<color=#00ff00>Don't wander too far off course, there is nothing else to find. The map displays all relevant points of interest.</color>
<color=#00ff00>This is the last cry of Refuge. Remember us.</color>

Chinese (simplified):
@d0 <color=#00ff00>这个实验性的神经接口允许1到4名参与者体验一名士兵生命最后时刻的虚拟现实模拟.</color>
<color=#00ff00>虚拟现实结构本质上是实验性的,因此所有参与者尽可能地保持彼此接近以避免打破虚拟现实矩阵是至关重要的。如果第一次没有成功,你可以多次尝试.</color>
@p9 @d0 <color=#00ff00>接口入口在激活后将保持打开状态2分钟,然后关闭状态5分钟。在进入模拟之前,请确保所有参与者都准备好并装备齐全.</color>
<color=#00ff00>在进入模拟之前,请确保所有参与者都穿着他们喜欢的盔甲.</color>
@p9 @d0 <color=#00ff00>在进入模拟之前,所有参与者应确保任务</color><color=#ff00ff>亡灵之章 2</color><color=#00ff00> 目前在他们的PDA中是活跃的。在你必须重新开始之前,你将有60分钟的时间来成功完成模拟. </color>
<color=#00ff00>不要偏离轨道太远,没有别的东西可找。地图显示了所有相关的兴趣点.</color>
<color=#00ff00>这是避难所最后的呼喊。记得我们.</color>

English:
@q0 @d0<b><color=#fafe10>[ IDA ]</color></b>
@d3<color=#00fbff>There is a clone chamber here. It seems they wanted to make sure you'd make it to the penal colony alive. How nice of them. If you do meet an unfortunate end, you can select this as a respawn location.</color>
@w3<color=#00fbff>First thing's first, you need to find a way out of your cell. @w2The door appears to still be locked, so no going out the front.</color>
@w2<color=#00fbff>Look around for any damage to the cell walls. Maybe there's a crack large enough for you to crawl through.</color>

Chinese (simplified):
@q0 @d0 <b><color=#fafe10>[ IDA ]</color></b>
@d3 <color=#00fbff>这里有一个克隆室。看起来他们想确保你能活着到达监狱殖民地。他们真贴心。如果你不幸遇难,你可以选择这里作为复活地点。</color>
@w3 <color=#00fbff>首先,你需要找到一种方法逃离你的囚室。@w2 门似乎还是锁着的,所以不能从前门出去。</color>
@w2 <color=#00fbff>四处看看,看看囚室墙壁上是否有损坏。也许有一个足够大的裂缝让你爬过去。</color>

English:
@q0 @d0<b><color=#fafe10>[ IDA ]</color></b>
@d3<color=#00fbff>Certainly, commander. @w2This appears to be a rudimentary lock. Standard issue on civilian transports. Should be easy enough to bypass. @w2And... @w2Done. @w2You now have access to your equipment. There's just one tiny problem...</color>
@p9<color=#00fbff>There's no armor locker in the armory to help you put on your standard issue Medium Armor. You're really going to want that armor for what comes next.</color>
@w2<color=#00fbff>Good news is there is a medical bay across the hall that will very likely have an armor locker. @w3Bad news is the hallway is now depressurized and you will have to run into the medical bay and put on your armor before you suffocate.</color>
@w3<color=#00fbff>How good are you at holding your breath?</color>

