English:
@q0 @d0<b><color=#fafe10>[ IDA ]</color></b>
@d3<color=#00fbff>The schematics in my memory banks are not sufficient to construct a ship capable of leaving this planet and the ones in your PDA have been wiped.</color>
@w3<color=#00fbff>However, @w2 there might be a way to recover the deleted schematics.</color>
@w3<color=#00fbff>This planet appears dead, @w1 but may have been inhabited in the past. @w2 If you were to find any ruins which has an Alien Core, you could destroy the core with one of your weapons and I can analyze the remnants of it.</color>
@p9 @d3 <color=#00fbff>Using the data I gain from analyzing the destroyed Alien Core, it may be possible to begin to reconstruct the deleted schematics, @w1 including for devices such as small vessel thrusters, @w2 cockpits, @w2 and other necessary devices for creating a ship capable of orbital flight.</color>
@w3<color=#00fbff>With only limited data, you will need to carefully pick and choose which technology you want me to reconstruct. @w2 I have arranged these schematics into a Tech Tree </color><color=#ffff00>(F3)</color><color=#00fbff> for your convenience where you will be able to spend your Unlock Points.</color>

Chinese (simplified):
@q0 @d0 <b><color=#fafe10>[ IDA ]</color></b>
@d3 <color=#00fbff>我存储库中的蓝图不足以建造一艘能够离开这个星球的飞船,而你的 PDA 中的蓝图已经被清除了。</color>
@w3 <color=#00fbff>然而,@w2 可能有一种方法可以恢复已删除的蓝图。</color>
@w3 <color=#00fbff>这个星球看起来已经死了,@w1 但过去可能有人居住。@w2 如果你能找到任何有外星核心的废墟,你可以用你的武器之一摧毁核心,我可以分析它的残余物。</color>
@p9 @d3 <color=#00fbff>利用我从分析被摧毁的外星核心获得的数据,可能有可能开始重建已删除的蓝图,@w1 包括小型飞船推进器,@w2 驾驶舱,@w2 以及其他创建能够进行轨道飞行的飞船所需的必要设备。</color>
@w3 <color=#00fbff>由于数据有限,你将需要仔细选择你想要我重建的技术。@w2 我已经将这些蓝图安排成一个技术树 </color><color=#ffff00>(F3)</color><color=#00fbff> 方便你使用,你将能够在那里花费你的解锁点。</color>

English:
@d0Selecting a patrol vessel to spawn will spawn it in front of you after a short countdown.
This should only be used in space.

<color=#ffffff><i>Make sure to read and agree to the disclaimer before spawning any patrol vessels.</i></color>

@q0Ah hello, welcome to our ship! I am the quartermaster here.
I buy and sell various supplies,@w2 and my friend next to me deals in schematics.
From time to time we may even have some free supplies to offer you.
@p9Please continue your tour of the ship.@w3 When you are finished please come speak to me again and I'll see if I can find some supplies you can have.
I think the lead researcher is looking for you. You can head up one of the elevators to meet with him in the lab.

Chinese (simplified):
@q0 啊,你好,欢迎来到我们的飞船!我是这里的军需官。
我买卖各种物资,@w2 我旁边的那位朋友负责交易图纸。
时不时我们甚至可能有一些免费的物资可以提供给你。
@p9 请继续参观我们的飞船。@w3 当你参观完毕后请再次与我交谈,我会看看是否能找到一些你可以拥有的物资。
我认为主要研究员正在找你。你可以乘坐其中一部电梯去实验室与他见面。

English:
@q0The quartermaster on the main hangar deck deals with various supplies. Sometimes they may have free supplies available to you.
The schematic trader next to them deals with buying or selling various schematics. If you have extra schematics you can sell them there.
@p9The lab is where the lead researcher, research computer, and schematic computers are located.
The lead researcher can give you hints of things to explore.
The research computer can make use of navigational data to increase your warp drive range and data pads and progenitor data chips to increase your unlock points.
The schematic computer allows you to use schematics to unlock new crafting recipes.
@p9The bridge here is where you'll find the captain and briefing room. Captains may sometimes offer various missions. The captains in the Alpha, Beta, Delta, and Epsilon systems might need some help exploring those systems if you speak to them.
There may be additional services added to UCH Research Vessels over time, so don't take this as a complete list.

Chinese (simplified):
@q0主停机坪上的军需官负责各种物资。有时他们可能有免费物资提供给你。
旁边的图纸交易商负责购买或出售各种图纸。如果你有多余的图纸,可以在那里出售。
@p9实验室是首席研究员、研究计算机和图纸计算机的所在地。
首席研究员可以给你提供探索的线索。
研究计算机可以使用导航数据来增加你的翘曲引擎范围,使用数据板和先祖数据芯片来增加你的解锁点数。
图纸计算机允许你使用图纸来解锁新的制造配方。
@p9这里的舰桥是你可以找到舰长和简报室的地方。舰长有时会提供各种任务。如果你和他们交谈,Alpha、Beta、Delta和Epsilon星系的舰长可能需要一些帮助来探索这些星系。
随着时间的推移,UCH研究船可能会增加额外的服务,所以不要将其视为完整列表。

English:
@q0That is correct. @w2If we have any hope of locating the Copernicus, we need to know who attacked them and why.
@w2The captain would have not continued the expedition if his ship was in danger without a very good reason.
@w2I need you to meet with this miner and obtain the coordinates to the wreckage he found.
@p9 @d3He mentioned he was currently staying at a Free Colonist Distribution Center in the region of Prosperity.
@w2Distribution Centers can be found in Trade Station Sectors inside Free Colonists territory in Prosperity. @w2Your map will identify them on the solar system map with a white station icon.
@p9 @d3You may have to pay for the information if you're not honored to the Free Colonists, so make sure you have 50,000 credits in your bank account @w1or bring along an {Loc(Item2)} or {Loc(Item3)} for trade.
@w3You may also have to perform some scanning, so stock up on a few survey probes and make sure your ship is equipped with a science station and scanning station.

Chinese (simplified):
@q0 没错。@w2 如果我们希望找到Copernicus,我们需要知道谁攻击了他们以及为什么。
@w2 如果船处于危险之中,舰长不会继续探险,除非有非常好的理由。
@w2 我需要你与这个矿工会面,获取他发现的残骸的坐标。
@p9 @d3 他提到他目前住在Prosperity地区的自由殖民者分销中心。
@w2 分销中心可以在Prosperity自由殖民者领土内的贸易空间站星区找到。@w2 你的地图将在太阳系地图上用白色站点图标标识它们。
@p9 @d3 如果你不受自由殖民者的尊敬,你可能需要为信息付费,所以确保你的银行账户里有50,000信用点@w1 ,或者带上一个{Loc(Item2)}或{Loc(Item3)}进行交易。
@w3 你可能还需要进行一些扫描,所以储备一些调查探针,并确保你的飞船配备了科学站和扫描站。

English:
@q0We really don't know how dangerous this mission will be, but I would rather make sure that you're prepared.
@w2You should bring a Capital Vessel equipped with advanced CPU extenders and specialized for heavy combat.
@w2The Copernicus was a state of the art UCH Research Vessel, @w1not your typical target for pirates.
@w2Whomever attacked them had to have been strong, and whatever the Copernicus found out there had to have been worth putting their crew in danger.
@w2I am not going to lie to you {Player.Name}, @w1this may be a dangerous mission that risks your ship.

Chinese (simplified):
@q0 我们真的不知道这个任务会有多危险,但我希望确保你做好准备。
@w2 你应该带来一艘装备了先进的CPU扩展器并专门用于重型战斗的主力舰。
@w2 哥白尼号是一艘最先进的UCH研究船,@w1 不是典型的海盗目标。
@w2 攻击他们的人必须非常强大,而哥白尼号在那里发现的东西必须值得让他们的船员置身于危险之中。
@w2 我不会对你撒谎 {Player.Name},@w1 这可能是一个危险的任务,可能会危及你的飞船。

English:
@q0So we have wrecks from an unknown faction with combat damage consistent with UCH weapon fire.
@w3Some kind of structure that was being constructed on an asteroid, @w2also consistent with this unknown faction.
@w3A piece of hull plating that appears to have been ripped off the Copernicus.
@w3And a warp trail leading further into the Dronelands. @w3Well, @w3This raises more questions than answers.

Chinese (simplified):
@q0 所以我们有来自未知派系的残骸,其战斗损伤与UCH武器的火力一致。
@w3 在小行星上正在建造的某种结构,@w2 也与这个未知派系一致。
@w3 一块看起来是从哥白尼号上撕下来的船体装甲板。
@w3 还有一条翘曲轨迹通向无人机之地更深处。@w3 嗯,@w3 这引发了比答案更多的问题。

English:
@q0So far there are no signs of the Copernicus from your probes. Our only lead right now are these alien drones.
@w2I need you to get close enough to discover some of them using your ship's detector to get close range scans.
@p9 @d3I also need you to get some more of those drone processors, @w2preferably ones that aren't broken. @w2Ten processors should be enough.
@w2You should be able to obtain processors by destroying some of those drones. @w2I recommend trying to find some lone Scouts or Harvesters if you're not too confident in your combat capabilities.
@w3Oh, and find some palladium ingots and carbon substrate. @w2You can mine palladium on Barren class planets in the Dronelands and carbon substrate you should already know where to find. @w2You'll need some for the next step.

Chinese (simplified):
@q0 到目前为止,从你的探测器中没有发现哥白尼号的迹象。我们现在唯一的线索是这些外星无人机。
@w2 我需要你用你的飞船探测器靠近它们,进行近距离扫描。
@p9 @d3 我还需要你获取更多的无人机处理器,@w2 最好是没有损坏的。@w2 十个处理器应该足够了。
@w2 你可以通过摧毁一些无人机来获得处理器。@w2 如果你对自己的战斗能力不够自信,我建议你试着找一些孤立的侦察机或收割机。
@w3 哦,还有找到一些钯锭和碳基材料。@w2 你可以在Dronelands的贫瘠类行星上开采钯,而碳基材料你应该已经知道在哪里找到。@w2 你下一步会需要它们。

English:
@q0The smallest drones appear to be built for scouting or harvesting resources.
@w2They are poorly armed and have weak shields, but are seldom alone.
@w2I have categorized many of these drones under the generic names of Scout or Harvester.
@w2Sometimes individual drones can join together to form a Small Swarm.

Chinese (simplified):
@q0 最小的无人机似乎是为了侦察或收集资源而建造的。
@w2 它们武装简陋,护盾薄弱,但很少单独行动。
@w2 我将这些无人机归类为侦察机或收割机的通用名称。
@w2 有时个别无人机可以联合起来形成一个小型蜂群。

English:
@q0I have identified several types of structures such as nests or assemblers.
@w2The size and strength of these seems to depend on their age.
@w2I have given them a prefix depending on their relative strength. @w2The prefixes are @w1Budding, @w1Brood, @w1Swarm, @w1 and Hive.
@w4These are just general categories however, as individual drones can vary and there may be many types not yet detected.

Chinese (simplified):
@q0 我已经识别出几种结构,如巢穴或组装器。
@w2 这些的大小和强度似乎取决于它们的年龄。
@w2 我根据它们的相对强度给它们加上了前缀。@w2 前缀是@w1 萌芽、@w1 群落、@w1 蜂群、@w1 和蜂巢。
@w4 这些只是一般类别,因为个别无人机可能会有所不同,可能还有许多尚未检测到的类型。

English:
@d0Dear {Player.Name}, I hope this message finds you well over in {Player.PlayfieldName}.
Don't be surprised to learn I know where you are. I have been keeping a close eye on you. You might call me an admirer of sorts.
I write to you today with an opportunity for both of us. A win-win as you Terrans are so fond of saying.
I have seen that you are an individual of questionable morals, and I have a problem that needs someone who isn't afraid to get their hands dirty.
@p9 @d0Several colonist freighters have fallen behind on paying their insurance dues and are no longer insured. I need you to pay one of them a visit and give them a gentle reminder to renew their insurance policy before something bad happens to them. I think once the news spreads the others will be more than eager to pay up.
@p9 @d0It's important that you only disable their ship, not destroy it. Try to avoid targeting their cores or generators as dead clients can't pay their dues and other freighter captains won't trust you for a period of time.
Destroy their rear thrusters to force them to come to a complete stop and then board their ship and find the captain on the bridge. Tell the captain you are there to collect their insurance premium. Also demand to take one of their officers to make sure that future payments are delivered on time.
@p9 @d0You can find these colonist freighters in most planetary orbits in habitable systems in neutral or Free Colonists territory.
Let me know if this sounds enticing to you. I eagerly await your reply.

Chinese (simplified):
@d0 亲爱的 {Player.Name},我希望这封信能在 {Player.PlayfieldName} 找到你,并且你一切都好。
不要惊讶地发现我知道你在哪里。我一直在密切关注你。你可以称我为某种仰慕者。
我今天写信给你,是为了我们双方都有机会。正如你们地球人常说的,双赢。
我看到你是一个道德可疑的个体,而我有一个问题需要一个不怕弄脏手的人。
@p9 @d0 有几艘殖民者货船拖欠了他们的保险费,并且不再有保险。我需要你去拜访其中一艘,并温和地提醒他们续保,以免发生不好的事情。我认为一旦消息传开,其他人将会非常乐意支付。
@p9 @d0 重要的是你只能使他们的船只失去动力,而不是摧毁它。尽量避免瞄准他们的核心或发电机,因为死去的客户无法支付他们的费用,而且其他货船船长在一段时间内不会信任你。
摧毁他们的后推进器,迫使他们完全停下来,然后登上他们的船只,在舰桥上找到船长。告诉船长你是来收取他们的保险费的。还要求带走他们的一名官员,以确保未来的付款能够按时交付。
@p9 @d0 你可以在大多数宜居星系的行星轨道上,在中立或自由殖民者领土上找到这些殖民者货船。
告诉我这是否对你有吸引力。我热切地等待你的回复。

English:
@q0 @d0Excellent job! Yes, of course I was watching.
Word will spread and the other colonists will think twice before being late on their payments ever again.
Speaking of payment, feel free to keep that payment you got from the freighter captain. Consider it your payment for a job well done.
You and I will do great things together, I know it. Don't bother trying to contact me. I will contact you.
@p9 @d0I have attached a data packet on what I know about freighter ransoming. I hope it will help you in your continued piracy.
@p9 @d0<color=#ffff00>Freighter Ransoming:</color>
<color=#ffffff>To ransom a freighter you must maintain at least neutral reputation with the Pirate Clans.</color>
<color=#ffffff>First disable the freighter by destroying the rear thrusters. The core and at least one generator must remain operational otherwise the captain will refuse to negotiate.</color>
@p9 @d0<color=#ffffff>Board the freighter and speak to the captain on the bridge to make your demands. The captain may refuse.</color>
<color=#ffffff>The higher your pirate reputation, the more types of demands you can make and the higher the chance the captain will pay ransom.</color>
<color=#ffffff>You are free to loot the freighter, but destroying the freighter's cores may result in other freighter captains refusing your ransom demands for a period of time as news of your untrustworthiness spreads.</color>

Chinese (simplified):
@q0 @d0 干得漂亮!当然,我一直在看着。
消息会传开,其他殖民者在再次拖欠付款之前会三思而后行。
说到付款,你可以随意保留从货船舰长那里得到的付款。把它当作你出色工作的报酬。
你和我将会一起做大事,我知道。不要试图联系我。我会联系你的。
@p9 @d0 我已经附上了一份关于货船勒索的数据包。我希望它能帮助你在持续的海盗活动中。
@p9 @d0 <color=#ffff00>货船勒索:</color>
<color=#ffffff>要勒索货船,你必须至少保持与海盗部落的中立声誉。</color>
<color=#ffffff>首先通过摧毁后部推进器来使货船失去动力。核心和至少一个发电机必须保持运行,否则舰长会拒绝谈判。</color>
@p9 @d0 <color=#ffffff>登上货船,与桥上的舰长交谈以提出你的要求。舰长可能会拒绝。</color>
<color=#ffffff>你的海盗声誉越高,你可以提出的要求类型就越多,舰长支付赎金的机会就越大。</color>
<color=#ffffff>你可以自由地掠夺货船,但摧毁货船的核心可能会导致其他货船舰长在你一段时间内拒绝你的赎金要求,因为你不可靠的消息传开。</color>

English:
I don't get out much but I have picked up a thing or two I am willing to pass along to you.
@w2Of course the simplest is buy low, sell high. @w2If you find a trader who sells something for cheap and another trader who buys that thing for more, @w2well, @w1you got yourself a trade route.
@p9There is of course another option. @w2If you ask around on stations or factories you can often find someone who is desperate for an item they do not have. @w2These individuals will often pay well above market value for those items and one could make a good profit.
@p9There is also space trucking. @w2What? @w1Don't look at me like that. @w1It's a legitimate career.
@w2There are orbital stations and factories in the territories of each major faction who will pay well for someone to ferry large volume goods back and forth to the other territories. @w2The trips are long and boring but it can be steady profit from what I have heard.

Chinese (simplified):
我不太经常外出,但我确实学到了一两件东西,我愿意把它们传授给你。
@w2 当然最简单的方法是低买高卖。@w2 如果你找到一个商人以低价卖东西,然后又找到一个愿意以更高价格买那个东西的商人,@w2 那么,@w1 你就为自己找到了一条贸易路线。
@p9 当然,还有另一种选择。@w2 如果你在站点或工厂周围打听,你通常可以找到一个急需他们没有的东西的人。@w2 这些人通常愿意以高于市场价值的价格支付这些物品,这样可以获得不错的利润。
@p9 还有太空货运。@w2 什么?@w1 别那样看着我。@w1 这是一份合法的职业。
@w2 在每个主要派系的领土上,有轨道站和工厂愿意为某人运送大量货物往来其他领土支付高额费用。@w2 据我听说,虽然旅程漫长而乏味,但可以获得稳定的收益。

English:
@d0<color=#ff00ff>The Prototype Micro Jump Drive is currently in experimental testing and you use it <u><b>AT YOUR OWN RISK.</b></u></color>
<color=#ffff00>This means using it could lead to unexpected problems including but not limited to disappearing ships and corrupted save games.</color>
